{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78392ed6-a61b-4f52-a10b-3beac805612a","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_4FYokz6YnYbxihbHvEDFpf","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-933756854e0646f5a01a3c65473e1769/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-933756854e0646f5a01a3c65473e1769/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4eee6ece-8e89-4656-8b30-612b65a18f3a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain` - it depends on `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"5C04:28D4C6:1CEFDE3:20BD5A5:6A07C84D"},"id":"242d5a16-2859-407a-a28b-4c0479965def","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:53.145Z","parentId":"07a28181-d2a0-4652-b4f2-c0b33a9d7a7e"}
